# MCP_TOPOLOGY.md

<!-- INSTRUCTION: This file declares the repo's relationship to the three MCP surfaces. No credential values, no API keys, no OAuth tokens. Pointer-shaped only. -->

## 1. Per-user stdio MCPs

<!-- INSTRUCTION: This surface lives at ~/.claude.json mcpServers. It is operator-scoped and not repo-propagated. Name server ids only if helpful. -->

Location: `~/.claude.json` `mcpServers`
Scope: operator/user scoped
Repo propagation: no

Common server-name examples: `MCP_DOCKER`, `playwright`, `tcc-fidelity-staging`

## 2. Repo-root HTTP MCPs

<!-- INSTRUCTION: Declare whether this repo advertises HTTP MCPs through <repo-root>/.mcp.json. Name server ids only; no URLs with secrets, headers, or tokens. -->

Location: `<repo-root>/.mcp.json`
Present in this repo: {{REPO_ROOT_MCP_PRESENT_YES_NO}}
Advertised server ids: {{REPO_ROOT_MCP_SERVER_IDS_OR_NONE}}

Example: NETA ETT advertises `supabase` as a repo-root HTTP MCP.

## 3. Claude.ai OAuth-brokered integrations

<!-- INSTRUCTION: This surface is user-scoped by OAuth construction and not repo-propagated. Name product classes only when useful. -->

Location: `~/.claude/mcp-needs-auth-cache.json` and related user cache
Scope: user scoped
Repo propagation: no

Common integration examples: Box, Figma, Vercel, Supabase, Mermaid Chart

## 4. Disjointness rule

Server names should remain disjoint across surfaces. If a same-name collision occurs in future, repo-root config wins for that repo.

No credential values belong in this file.
